###How to fix the App Dependencies issue of node-forge:0.10.0 of pkg:npm/node-forge@0.10.0 in apache web server and which owasp top 10 web 2021 category this issue belong to ?
To fix the App Dependencies issue of node-forge:0.10.0 of pkg:npm/node-forge@0.10.0 in apache web server, you can follow these steps:

1. Update the node-forge package to a newer version. You can do this by running the following command:

```
npm install -g node-forge@latest
```

2. Restart the apache web server.

This issue belongs to the OWASP Top 10 Web 2021 category of **A1 - Injection**. This category includes vulnerabilities that allow an attacker to inject malicious code into a web application. This can be done through a variety of methods, such as SQL injection, cross-site scripting (XSS), and command injection.

The node-forge package is a JavaScript library that provides a variety of cryptographic functions. It is a popular package, but it has been known to contain vulnerabilities. The vulnerability in node-forge:0.10.0 allows an attacker to execute arbitrary code on the server by injecting malicious code into a web application.

By updating the node-forge package to a newer version, you can mitigate the risk of this vulnerability. You should also keep your web applications up to date with the latest security patches to help protect them from other vulnerabilities.

Here are some additional tips for preventing injection vulnerabilities:

* Use prepared statements instead of dynamic SQL.
* Sanitize all user input before using it in a web application.
* Use a web application firewall (WAF) to help protect your web applications from common injection attacks.
